text: Way too harsh on both counts. Insofar as Chris Rufo is 'at the helm' it's because he took the initiative in launching a (seemingly Quixotic) campaign against Woke tyranny when the right was completely lost in the wilderness. Reframing him as some kind of braking mechanism on MAGA momentum is simply bizarre.
I'll admit only that a little smacking around was understandable in that case.
Meanwhile ...
C'mon. Who else has come close to actual combat engagement with the enemy at his level? Lot's of hard MAGA talk. Rufo is actually getting woke apparatchiks canned.
Everyone has the occasional off moment.
Over-sensitive much.
Crucial document, thanks.
Lunacy.

Bringing Panda Express into the discussion probably wasn't the best available move. 
Lemurs are enjoying 'Panda Express Time' though.
The Anglo-Protestant Whig Tradition isn't a dinner party.
So much potential Panda Express management talent wasting itself on X drama, I can't even ...

My (heavy whitepill abuser) take on recent X MAGA drama is that the administration command core will keep people out of roles they're likely to be weak in. Trump told RFK that he wasn't touching energy policy. Vivek isn't going to touch immigration policy. It's going to be okay.
Is he, though?
Tom Homan, Stephen Miller -- these are the hardest migration control guys imaginable. There's no way Trump is installing them by accident.
Same energy from Samuel Johnson (on Americans): "Sir, they are a race of convicts, and ought to be thankful for any thing we allow them short of hanging."
What if he's good at identifying slabs of federal government for surgical removal? It's not as if that's impossible to imagine. (And no one's appointing him H1b Czar anytime soon.)
Harsh.

Bold prophecy (in parenthesis). 
I'm wildly in love with Vivek relative to everyone else on my TL, but he's looking seriously toasted.
On the bright side, MAGA's genius at vacuuming up the communist tendency of the Anglo-Protestant Whig Tradition is a thing of wonder.
... "All your ornery egalitarianism belong to us now."
